>coille</i> ‘wood’ + the placename forming suffix <i>-in</i>. Alternatively, from the lands of Kelloe in the barony of Hume (Berwickshire), whose name is of uncertain origin."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Kelley was born in 1178, in South Tawton, Devon, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Kelley, was 32 and her mother, Mrs. John Kelly, was 26. She married William de Wrey about 1200, in Wyke, Devon, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1178–":"1178–Surnud","1178–Female":"1178–Surnud","1170–1248":"1170–1248","1210–1248":"1210–1248","1213–1248":"1213–1248","1146–Male":"1146–Surnud","1152–Female":"1152–Surnud","1248":"1248","1213":"1213","1146":"1146","1178":"1178","1210":"1210","about 1200":"umbes 1200","1152":"1152","1172":"1172","about 1210":"umbes 1210","1170":"1170","North Wyke, South Tawton, Devon, England":"South Tawton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wyke, Devon, England":"Wyke, Devon, England"},"fi":{"1178–":"1178–Kuollut","1178–Female":"1178–Kuollut","1170–1248":"1170–1248","1210–1248":"1210–1248","1213–1248":"1213–1248","1146–Male":"1146–Kuollut","1152–Female":"115